text: The Biskopsgården Church () is a church building in the southern parts of Biskopsgården on the island of Hisingen in the town of Gothenburg in Sweden. It belongs to the Lundby of the Church of Sweden. It was opened in 1961. It was originally called the Southern Biskopsgården Church () until the Northern Biskopsgården Church was taken out of use in 2004. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:Church of Sweden churches Category:Churches in Gothenburg Category:1961 establishments in Sweden
